Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.90,0:00:04.10,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Allow me to congratulate you \Non your upcoming nuptials.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:07.61,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I am Kaine Tully, from \Nthe Aria Trading Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.40,0:00:11.17,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.17,0:00:14.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming such \Na long way to meet with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.99,0:00:19.92,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,This really is a lovely \Ntime of year, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.42,0:00:19.92,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He's as impressive as I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:23.03,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Just meeting his eye makes me \Nfeel like he's seen through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:23.71,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, did you say your wedding will \Nbe in the middle of the eighth month?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.71,0:00:27.00,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But since I know him well, I \Nshould have the upper hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.71,0:00:27.00,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,That means you'll become a \Nbride under the summer skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.30,0:00:32.01,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,To have such a beautiful lady as \Nthe future mother of the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.30,0:00:32.01,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In order to avoid the war, \Nand to live a long life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.01,0:00:35.01,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,I must say I'm jealous of \Nthe people of Galkhein.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.01,0:00:35.01,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I will have you lend me your aid, chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:41.94,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sure you've already heard, but \NI want everything used in my wedding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.94,0:00:44.46,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,to be procured by the Aria Trading Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.46,0:00:47.77,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Well, well! You have no idea how \Nmuch I appreciate such a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.77,0:00:51.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, would it be possible \Nto see your wares right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:53.78,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.10,0:00:59.03,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I haven't a single item I would sell to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.36,0:02:35.58,top,Tully,0,0,0,,Oh, pardon me. It seems you've misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.58,0:02:37.96,top,Tully,0,0,0,,However, it's just as I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.96,0:02:42.01,main,Tully,0,0,0,,A lady such as yourself simply \Ncannot become a customer of ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:44.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,May I ask why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.59,0:02:49.77,main,Tully,0,0,0,,The items which we are able to procure \Naren't in keeping with your level of resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:51.15,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Resolve?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.11,0:02:56.53,main,Tully,0,0,0,,It seems that, for some reason, you're \Nstaking your life on this transaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:00.64,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I've seen many different people in my time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:05.03,main,Tully,0,0,0,,but you seem to have a stronger \Nresolve than any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.44,0:03:10.82,main,Tully,0,0,0,,This despite the fact that you're only \Nbuying wedding goods from a simple trader, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:13.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, it is a once-in-a-lifetime event.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.68,0:03:16.01,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I've allowed myself to \Nbecome overenthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.01,0:03:18.46,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm so inexperienced. \NIt's quite embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.30,0:03:24.30,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Please, rest at ease. I'm certain your \Nwedding ceremony will be splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.30,0:03:29.66,main,Tully,0,0,0,,However, unfortunately, our wares \Nseem to be inadequate to the task.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:32.61,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Thank you for your offer. It's been an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:34.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Ch-Chief Tully!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:38.57,main,Tully,0,0,0,,All else aside, Galkhein is quite \Nan impressive country, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:45.47,main,Tully,0,0,0,,We're thinking of forgetting our work for a \Nwhile and spending a few days enjoying the sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.41,0:03:49.02,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please wait! If we could \Nspeak a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.02,0:03:53.50,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Farewell, beautiful future crown princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.16,0:04:10.72,flashback italics,Tully,0,0,0,,Listen well, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:13.72,flashback,Tully,0,0,0,,Become a merchant who can pick her customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:18.98,flashback,Tully,0,0,0,,Offer wares or other value that \Nthey can only get through us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:23.53,flashback,Tully,0,0,0,,When you do that, then we're the \Nones who can choose our customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:27.32,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I couldn't make the chief choose me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:32.40,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But I'll need his connections when the Aria \NTrading Company spreads across the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.20,0:04:35.90,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Um, Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.98,0:04:40.87,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Why is the future crown \Nprincess working in a garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:46.09,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold gave me this plot, so \NI thought I'd grow medicinal plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:49.60,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Depending on how I mix them, I'll be \Nable to make all sorts of medicines.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.98,0:04:52.10,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:57.44,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Still, was he simply being wary of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:03.18,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He is a cautious man, but he also \Nloves an all-or-nothing gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.67,0:05:06.80,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Have I overlooked something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.77,0:05:14.08,flashback,Tully,0,0,0,,We're thinking of forgetting our work for a \Nwhile and spending a few days enjoying the sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.47,0:05:17.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's the end of my \Ngardening this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.76,0:05:19.25,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,A-Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:23.51,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm going to rest in my room. I'll \Nleave guarding the halls to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:24.76,main,Kamil; Dennis,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, my lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:31.01,main,Chester,0,0,0,,Still, are you sure about this, chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:33.89,main,Chester,0,0,0,,You're kicking aside a way to make \Nhuge money from the crown princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:38.44,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You dummy. If we took that lady on \Nas a customer, we'd see heavy losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:44.51,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Chief Tully.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:45.03,top,traders,0,0,0,,I can't drink any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:47.03,top,traders,0,0,0,,You win, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:51.91,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I did think you might deign \Nto visit us soon, but this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:05:55.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, that was an invitation after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:05:56.98,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.24,0:06:01.29,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I'm astounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:04.19,main,Tully,0,0,0,,To think you'd outdrink \Nmy men while you waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.19,0:06:08.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Since they're such enjoyable company, \Nthe drink just kept flowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.63,0:06:12.26,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Setting that aside, that dye has \Ntaken quite beautifully to your hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.72,0:06:15.70,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,My hair color tends to \Nstand out a bit, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:21.87,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If I told you I'd sell you the method, \Nwould you be open to negotiations with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.66,0:06:24.15,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I would never!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.15,0:06:28.65,main,Tully,0,0,0,,After all, you've brought something\N even more lucrative, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:34.43,main,Tully,0,0,0,,And now, just as you wished, \Nwe will begin our negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.43,0:06:36.09,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Let's start with a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.09,0:06:37.58,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Just one thing first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:41.79,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,While we're here, please speak freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.19,0:06:46.55,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,When he speaks so formally to \Nme, it sets me off-balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:49.55,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Well, if you insist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:07:03.46,main,Tully,0,0,0,,So, milady, no more of this "I want a \Ndress for my wedding" charade, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:08.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Of course. It's obvious that trying \Nsuch tricks on you won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:09.36,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:12.36,main,Tully,0,0,0,,My intuition is telling me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:17.62,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, it says that I should take you \Non not as a client, but as a trading partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.14,0:07:21.03,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I won't help with a plan \Nif I don't know the full scope of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.03,0:07:25.31,main,Tully,0,0,0,,But don't worry, despite appearances, \NI'm very dedicated to my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.31,0:07:31.13,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I can promise you whatever profits, no, \Neven greater profits than you've imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:36.26,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Now, how about you spill every last detail \Nof this money-making scheme of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:38.27,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I can't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.99,0:07:39.80,main,Tully,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.61,0:07:43.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I can't tell you about my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:48.28,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even so, I want the Aria Trading \NCompany to become my ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:51.58,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You say the most interesting things, milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:55.21,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You want me to enter into a contract \Nwithout being told anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.21,0:07:57.01,main,Tully,0,0,0,,and it isn't even certain \Nthat I'll profit from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:08:00.27,main,Tully,0,0,0,,This is the type of offer \Nthat traders hate the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.27,0:08:02.47,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I will, of course, prepare compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:07.29,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You're telling me to just trust you when \Nyou say I'll make a profit? A fine idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:09.54,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Within the next few years,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:12.67,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,the crown prince of this nation \Nwill wage wars on other countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.67,0:08:17.55,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and I'm formulating a plan to stop him... but \Nit's not as though I can tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:19.27,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Listen well, milady,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.27,0:08:22.94,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I trust my intuition a great deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.94,0:08:25.69,main,Tully,0,0,0,,but what I regard as even more \Nimportant is results and—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.69,0:08:28.23,main,Rishe; overlapped,0,0,0,,Results and proof of performance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.05,0:08:34.84,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I will think of a business which will \Nprove successful here in the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:38.69,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you deem me worthy of \Nyour trust because of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:41.66,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,then may I ask that you reevaluate \Nthis decision at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.46,0:08:48.84,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:51.61,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You're saying that if your idea \Nseems likely to turn a profit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.61,0:08:53.66,main,Tully,0,0,0,,you want me to acknowledge you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:55.59,main,Tully,0,0,0,,That's exactly the sort of thing I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:57.84,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Yes, I know that very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.07,0:09:02.46,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You have a week. I'm looking \Nforward to this, milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.46,0:09:04.45,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then it's a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:10.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you for your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.63,0:09:15.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And when everyone wakes, please \Nhave them drink this medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.61,0:09:18.12,main,Tully,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:21.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I think you'll understand \Nquickly once you use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.93,0:09:30.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It isn't a simple thing to \Nsneak out of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.95,0:09:39.51,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You were out late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.61,0:09:42.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.76,0:09:45.50,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I heard that your offer \Nof trade was turned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.70,0:09:48.58,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's a strange story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:53.61,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,A simple trader rejecting a request \Nfrom a future crown princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.48,0:09:58.22,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'm the one who said to \Nspend your time as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.22,0:10:02.03,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,That's why I believe it would be \Nunreasonable of me to criticize your actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:04.09,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,so I awaited your return instead. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.36,0:10:43.69,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,So, even you look like that \Nwhen faced with a man alone at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.80,0:10:52.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I... am very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:11:00.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Sneaking out of the villa alone at night is \Nunbecoming of my position as your fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:01.62,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If your reputation were damaged because—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.62,0:11:03.31,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I don't care about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.23,0:11:08.02,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're not hurt, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:08.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:12.52,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.73,0:11:18.69,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,From now on, whenever you visit \Ntown, I will go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:19.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.53,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I told you. You're free to do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.53,0:11:25.47,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I also told you that I \Nwould help you in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.47,0:11:29.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Oh, but... I couldn't possibly ask Your \NHighness to go along with my selfish behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.80,0:11:32.06,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I said that you're free to do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:34.58,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I didn't say you're free \Nto put yourself in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.29,0:11:37.17,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.48,0:11:39.67,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're much too indulgent with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:42.43,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well, as it's you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:45.87,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,if I try to restrict you by saying that \Nyou're never allowed to visit town again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.87,0:11:47.84,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,you'd just slip out quietly \Nagain, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:50.23,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Even if it meant dyeing your hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.99,0:11:55.19,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Giving permission with conditions attached \Nseems more likely to work as a restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:58.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Am I really so easily understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:11:59.11,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.64,0:12:03.75,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're the type that's so difficult to \Nunderstand that I can't predict you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.60,0:12:07.44,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're enjoying this, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.44,0:12:09.74,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You and the chief both.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.36,0:12:11.72,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.40,0:12:15.96,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What has passed between you \Nand the Aria Trading Company?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.68,0:12:19.69,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.69,0:12:20.59,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.01,0:12:23.09,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Do you happen to be hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:03.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Um, Y-Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:06.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,There's something I must apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.73,0:13:07.64,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:13.99,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry, even though \NI'm the one who proposed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.58,0:13:15.71,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:19.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm a terrible cook!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.28,0:13:24.30,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.07,0:13:27.08,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:31.99,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well, it's unusual to find a noble \N lady who has experience cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:39.09,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In my past lives, meals were just a time \Nwhen I prioritized putting food in my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.99,0:13:43.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I don't think this soup will \Nsuit your tastes, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.99,0:13:48.01,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:48.79,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.00,0:13:51.76,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,This soup will do just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.19,0:13:56.50,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I don't think he can tell \Ngood flavors from bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:13:56.50,top,Arnold,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.50,0:13:58.90,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're thinking something \Ndisrespectful, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:00.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.33,0:14:04.06,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:06.02,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's your fault that I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.47,0:14:08.12,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Let's hurry up and set out the dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.69,0:14:09.66,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:13.66,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Which is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:18.23,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I now have to propose a new \Nbusiness idea within a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:21.21,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:22.56,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Which means?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:24.67,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I said I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.67,0:14:27.30,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I comprehend what it is you want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.46,0:14:33.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're not going to ask me what I plan \Nto use the Aria Trading Company for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.07,0:14:36.89,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You kept that a secret from the \Ntrading company, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:39.06,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Then, I can't imagine that you'd tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:40.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's just as you say, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.32,0:14:44.60,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Have you figured out this business \Nor whatever you're thinking up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.60,0:14:46.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have several ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.48,0:14:49.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's just that I don't know \Nif any of them will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.64,0:14:52.22,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What kinds of people live in the capital?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.22,0:14:54.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What sorts of things do they love?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.33,0:14:56.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,There's a mountain of \Nthings I need to research.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:14:59.51,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're saying this will be a difficult fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:00.35,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:07.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You really are enjoying this, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:09.74,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You should do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:11.92,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I have to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:13.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, of course. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.35,0:15:19.27,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:21.62,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Have you met my younger brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.62,0:15:24.35,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness's younger brother? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.35,0:15:25.52,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.75,0:15:28.82,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If he approaches you, don't entertain him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.82,0:15:30.28,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is there something I should know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:32.18,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,There's no need for you to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:54.40,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,This town's population, \Nits male to female ratio,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.40,0:15:57.27,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and its age distribution are \Nthe minimum information I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.27,0:15:59.18,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Changes in its economic development...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:01.31,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,the state of the surrounding regions...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:04.94,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,information on traders and travelers \Nentering and leaving, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:10.77,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I garden in the morning, check \Nteaching materials in the afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.77,0:16:13.45,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and I have to prepare for the \Nwedding ceremony as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:15.75,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I won't be getting any \Nsleep or rest for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:18.95,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,A midnight snack? You, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:20.03,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:21.00,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:24.00,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe must be an excellent cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.68,0:16:27.21,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,She said she's terrible at cooking...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:28.66,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,but it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:31.56,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:36.35,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Is adding medicinal herbs \Nto soup a standard practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.79,0:16:38.23,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,To soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.23,0:16:40.60,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,No, that isn't usually done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:42.98,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.67,0:16:51.86,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Were you unable to get much rest last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:54.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I was doing a little research.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:16:56.70,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Please don't push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.57,0:17:03.33,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe! Please stand back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.33,0:17:04.78,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Let's return to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.89,0:17:09.68,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Black hair is rare on this continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.68,0:17:10.90,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:13.95,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:14.75,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.68,0:17:20.05,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You are my older brother's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.50,0:17:26.52,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, my lovely older sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.94,0:17:29.81,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Finally, we meet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.81,0:17:33.04,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I've sent so many letters \Nsaying I wanted to meet you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:35.79,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,but my brother hasn't sent a single reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.79,0:17:37.07,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Isn't that just mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:43.08,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,There's no need to be so tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.14,0:17:46.07,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.07,0:17:48.06,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Theodore Auguste Hein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.06,0:17:52.34,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm second in line to the throne \Nand Arnold Hein's younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.74,0:17:55.65,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I've been told not to spend \Ntime with him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.65,0:18:00.61,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm honored to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.61,0:18:03.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,My name is Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.92,0:18:09.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A twist of fate has allowed me to fill the \Nlowest position in the imperial family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.00,0:18:11.14,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I hope that we will get on well together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:13.86,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I was wondering, what are you \Ndoing out here, dear sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.86,0:18:17.36,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This garden plot is one that I've created.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.36,0:18:18.88,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You made this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.88,0:18:21.30,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.30,0:18:23.91,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,It's rare to find a bed so fluffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.38,0:18:27.67,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,But there is one thing bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:28.92,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Will you look here for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:30.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.33,0:18:32.61,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,See? Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.72,0:18:35.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.61,0:18:38.09,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I want to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:44.84,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You poor thing. Dragged all \Nthe way to a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.84,0:18:48.43,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You aren't truly a bride. You're a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:51.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:52.86,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.75,0:18:58.15,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold is more than \Nsatisfactorily considerate toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.65,0:19:00.83,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:07.18,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm glad I was able to meet \Nyou today! I'll see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.18,0:19:16.17,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Second in line to the throne?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:20.00,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That's not something you say as an \Nintroduction to your older brother's fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:25.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This may seem apropos of nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.68,0:19:29.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but earlier, you didn't \Nseem your usual selves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.24,0:19:33.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Do you have orders not to let \Nme near his younger brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.25,0:19:37.52,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,That isn't something we \Nwould be able to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.52,0:19:41.15,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, do the brothers get along well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.88,0:19:44.57,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,We can't speak to that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.96,0:19:47.12,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for asking such strange questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:47.95,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.83,0:19:53.14,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'll have to deal with \Nthis matter eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.14,0:19:55.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,but right now, my negotiation \Nwith the chief comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:19:57.91,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Don't make me repeat myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.32,0:20:00.88,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Our military force will be \Nturned to the protection of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:02.57,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The decision has already been made.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:06.16,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,Ignoring the regional lords in order to \Ntenderheartedly protect the commoners?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.16,0:20:07.78,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.78,0:20:12.85,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The nobility has their private armies, and \Nthe nation provides the funds to maintain them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:14.03,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You can say whatever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.03,0:20:16.90,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,Your Highness, please reconsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.43,0:20:21.99,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,I can't say that your father \Nwill be pleased by this order.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.85,0:20:26.41,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I will not argue with you. Know your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.54,0:20:35.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.08,0:20:54.61,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'll have separate notices sent to the lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.61,0:20:56.68,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,Notices?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.68,0:21:01.19,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Our protecting the people just needs to \Nend up being in their favor, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:07.22,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If our forces are turned to protecting the \Npeople and they are able to live in safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.22,0:21:11.08,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,that will ultimately lead to increased tax \Nrevenue which should benefit the lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.75,0:21:19.09,main,Earl in military affairs,0,0,0,,If that's the case, then the lords \Nwill likely accept the change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:20.71,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,This conversation is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.90,0:21:28.28,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,The indemnities gained through war
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:31.97,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,are invested locally in revitalization \Nand creating employment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:35.60,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,This policy was created by Arnold Hein.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.64,0:21:40.99,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He is forcefully introducing \Npolicies which benefit the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:45.56,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He really is very different from the \Nimpressions I have of him from my past lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:51.18,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well then, good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.18,0:21:52.49,main,Dennis; Kamil,0,0,0,,Good night, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.59,0:22:06.84,sign_generic,text,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\an7\pos(6.409,261.138)\fs18}I will confide a secret to\Nyou. Be at the chapel\Ntonight at twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.59,0:22:06.84,sign_generic,text,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\pos(118.878,335.988)\fs18}Arnold Hein
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.08,0:22:27.65,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Good evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.65,0:22:29.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.58,0:22:32.03,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Good evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.42,0:22:34.10,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,my lovely older sister.
